      "content": "Your tomato plants are likely suffering from nitrogen deficiency or older leaf yellowing due to natural senescence, which is common in healthy growth cycles, but could also indicate a soil nutrient imbalance. To fix the soil, consider adding a balanced organic fertilizer or compost to replenish nutrients, while ensuring you water deeply to encourage root growth without waterlogging the roots. You should also prune a few of the lower yellow leaves to improve air circulation and redirect the plant's energy upward. If the issue persists, a soil test might be needed to identify specific deficiencies.",
